description: Remove placeholder UI and data when a section is client-approved
alwaysApply: true
---

# Content finalization

When copy, images, stats, reviews, map embeds, or gallery assets for a homepage section are approved, finalize that section and remove development placeholder treatment.

## Data (`src/data/`)

- Set `isFinalized: true` on the section export, or delete `placeholderNote` once no longer needed.
- Remove `provisional: true`, `isPlaceholder: true`, demo author names, and placeholder image paths.
- Use real alt text, captions, URLs, and verified figures only.

## Components (`src/components/sections/`)

Remove for finalized sections only:

- Footer disclaimer paragraphs sourced from `placeholderNote`
- Visible labels such as "To be confirmed", "Demo testimonial", "Placeholder image. Replace before launch"
- Overlay badges like "Demo video placeholder" or "Address to be confirmed" when real data exists
- Helper copy written only for unfinished assets

## Do not remove

- Form field `placeholder` attributes (input hints)
- Placeholder treatment on sections still awaiting approval
- Medical disclaimer in footer or other permanent legal copy

## Example

```js
// src/data/whyChoose.js — finalized
export const whyChooseContent = {
  isFinalized: true,
  eyebrow: "Qualified Experts",
  title: "Why Choose Rahman Plastic Surgery",
  image: { src: "/assets/why-choose.jpg", alt: "Confident patients at Rahman Plastic Surgery." },
  reasons: ["Board Certified Plastic Surgeon", "..."],
};
```

```jsx
// WhyChooseSection.jsx — no placeholderNote footer when finalized
{!whyChooseContent.isFinalized ? (
  <p className="mt-8 text-xs text-white/45">{whyChooseContent.placeholderNote}</p>
) : null}
```

Prefer deleting dead placeholder code entirely instead of leaving it commented out.
